The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Tuesday, August 30, 2005 

 IN THE CITY

 Talented youngsters Rakesh Krishnan, Sheikh Eklakh Ahmed and Md Ziauddin were included in the CAB squad for the Moin-ud-Dowlah Trophy in Hyderabad. The trio dropped from the side that played in Bangalore were Kamal Hasan Mondal, Sourav Sarkar and Anustup Majumder. Shib Shankar Paul will join the squad later after a stint at the MRF Academy.

 Bengal Motor Sports Club (BMSC) will organise the Tata Bearings Monsoon Rally for four and two-wheelers from September 9-11. 

 The Calcutta-Jamshedpur-Calcutta route will cover approximately 1000 km and traverse through forests and dirt tracks. Prize-money of Rs 1.83 lakh will be up for grabs, with the four-wheeler winner earning Rs 1.22 lakh. Entries close on September 5.

 Rama Das, a former India goalkeeper, passed away in the city on Monday. The 40-year-old was suffering from cancer.

 FOOTBALL: CFL Super Division: Calcutta Customs vs Md AC (Mohun Bagan); WB Police vs Peerless (Howrah). Matches from 3 pm.




